{"title":"Haro Bikes Gets “Crossed-Up” with Skwad LT 20″ Cargo Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/haro-bikes-skwad-lt-20-cargo-bike/","date":1699626489000,"content":"<p><img width=\"990\" height=\"660\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-blue-side-shot.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT blue side shot\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-blue-side-shot.jpeg 990w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-blue-side-shot-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-blue-side-shot-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-blue-side-shot-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-blue-side-shot-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-blue-side-shot-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Operating out of Vista, California, Haro Bikes released a new 20″ wheeled cargo eBike. The new Skwad LT sports a hub-driven, 250-watt motor, a low center of gravity, and is said to deliver a fast and balanced ride even when loaded.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT Gray side shot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Gray-side-shot.jpeg 990w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Haro Bikes) Matte Charcoal</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT hydro brakes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-hydro-brakes.jpeg 990w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT Hydro brkes rear\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Hydro-brkes-rear.jpeg 990w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The small wheels will make this bike easier to get around tight spaces and easily tuck away when not in use. The minimalist aluminum frame and fork are both attractive and strong. The Skwad uses a slim 36v, 300w “in-tube battery” for its power source and hydraulic brakes with a motor cut off. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT MX style bars and stem\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-MX-style-bars-and-stem.jpeg 990w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Handling the gear management is the trusty Shimano Altus shifter and rear derailleur. Paired with the Altus shifty bits, is a Shimano 8-speed cassette (12-28t). Pulling from Haro’s rich history in BMX the Skwad has a BMX-inspired two-piece handlebar and Haro Base Line BMX-styled stem. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT built in rear rack\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-built-in-rear-rack.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Skwad LT uses built-in, compatible AtranVelo System mounts to mount their available assortment of baskets, crates, and bags, allowing you to take full advantage of Skwad’s cargo-carrying abilities.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Skwad LT Rider’s App</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Rider’s App is used, like many others, to link the user to the Skwad LT via your phone. The app is said to offer the ability to give the user weather notifications, battery capacity updates, Bike status, diagnostics, navigation, assistance mode, home page, and your personal profile. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT on and off button\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-on-and-off-button.jpeg 990w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The app will collect info about your total mileage, average speed, and riding history record. The navigation feature includes a map function, route suggestion, estimated time of arrival (ETA), and even calculate for battery capacity in regard to the selected route. This feature will ensure you have enough battery capacity for the selected ride. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Skwad Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Geo-Chart.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"620\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Geo-Chart.jpeg\" alt=\"Haro Skwad LT Geo-Chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Geo-Chart.jpeg 620w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Geo-Chart-297x237.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Haro-Skwad-LT-Geo-Chart-120x96.jpeg 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><table><tbody><tr><th>A. Seat Tube (C-T)</th><td>360mm</td></tr><tr><th>B. Top Tube (Effective)</th><td>618mm</td></tr><tr><th>C. Head Angle</th><td>70°</td></tr><tr><th>D. Seat Angle</th><td>72.3°</td></tr><tr><th>E. Chainstay</th><td>400mm</td></tr><tr><th>F. Wheelbase</th><td>1090mm</td></tr><tr><th>G. Head Tube Length</th><td>250mm</td></tr><tr><th>H. Reach</th><td>425mm</td></tr><tr><th>Fork Height (A-C)</th><td>410mm</td></tr><tr><th>Fork Offset</th><td>40mm</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Skwad Features and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $2399</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Colors: Atlantic Blue and Matte Charcoal</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>250 W Rear Hub Motor</li>\n\n\n\n<li>20MPH Top Assisted Speed</li>\n\n\n\n<li>28 Mile Range</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Slim Intube Battery</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shimano Altus 8SPD</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sella Royal Essenza Saddle</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dual Piston Hydraulic Brakes With Motor Shut Off</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lezynne Front And rear lights</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Atran Velo Front and Rear Racks</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Haro Baseline Stem</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Haro 2-PC 3″ MX Bar</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bluetooth App With Navigation</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight: 50lbs</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://harobikes.com/products/skwad-lt\" target=\"_blank\"><em>harobikes.com</em></a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/haro-bikes-skwad-lt-20-cargo-bike/\">Haro Bikes Gets “Crossed-Up” with Skwad LT 20″ Cargo Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e3345534fddeab32e8d82c29f4e40947b1eb2cd3e8731e50cc2cc1c515a1f463","category":"Cycling"}